  "market_context": "Light Crude Oil Futures daily chart in early February 2024, following three consecutive bearish expansion days (open-high-low-close pattern), then a bullish reversal candle forming after sweeping the prior day's low, followed by a consolidation indecision candle.",
  "key_observation": "After three bearish directional days, price swept the previous day’s low and printed an open-low-high-close (bullish reversal) candle, then consolidated before resuming higher with another bullish expansion.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identify three consecutive bearish directional days, each showing open-high-low-close structure indicating strong downside momentum.",
    "Step 2: Observe the next day’s action: price sweeps the prior day’s low and closes inside the range, forming an open-low-high-close (bullish reversal) candle.",
    "Step 3: Note the following day’s expansion: price closes over the previous bar’s high, confirming continuation of the reversal bias.",
    "Step 4: Recognize the subsequent day as consolidation: open and close prices are nearly identical, indicating indecision and accumulation before the next move.",
    "Step 5: Analyze the next candle: price sweeps the prior day’s low into a fair value gap and forms another open-low-high-close reversal candle, triggering a move higher."
  ],
  "outcome": null,
  "lessons": "Daily OHLC sequencing (especially open-low-high-close reversals) reliably signals structural shifts after extended directional moves; consolidation after reversal often precedes continuation, not exhaustion.",
